Take two long weekends, add a couple of libational holidays, stir in a little icy weather, and you've got a recipe for the near hibernation evidenced in Broadway's corridors of power this week.

All across town, agents' offices were closed, producers were away, and the masters of spin were finding exciting new ways to fill time.

''My office is the cleanest it has ever been,'' said Chris Boneau of Boneau/Bryan-Brown, the theatrical publicity agency. ''And it's usually pretty clean.''

Even actors were getting time off. At the Cort Theater, the cast and crew of ''The Blue Room'' had scheduled four whole days off last week, apparently in line with the desire of the cast (read Nicole Kidman) to spend Christmas with family (read Tom Cruise and their children).